  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nSwipe buttons should always have an icon, and optionally text. The text should only be displayed if there's enough room.\r\n\r\nBut not all icons have been defined in [Figma Shell](https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=6105-546987&t=EIM0OQhjnArzVOmz-0), so double-check with designers.\r\n\r\nThis issue is currently blocked by the unmerged PR https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/15284.\r\n\r\nList of swipe buttons implemented:\r\n\r\n- Admin: accept and decline.\r\n- Contact request: accept, decline, and cancel.\r\n- Identity verification: decline, write reply, mark as untrustworthy, and mark as trusted.\r\n- Membership: accept or decline private group chat invitation\r\n\r\n### Example where the text doesn't fit the available width\r\n\r\nIn the image below, only the icon for _untrustworthy_ should be displayed, not the text because it's too long to fit.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/223685901-f59610a6-e83f-4d02-8fcd-e1f650b164b9.png)\r\n",
